@page "/sizes"

<div class="container mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-24">
    <section class="py-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 mb-6 tracking-tight">Images with <code>sizes</code> and <code>AspectRatio</code></h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
            Explore how to create responsive images that adapt to different screen sizes and maintain their intended proportions using the <code>sizes</code> and <code>AspectRatio</code> props.
        </p>

        <section class="mb-12 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden border border-gray-200">
            <div class="relative aspect-video bg-gray-100">
                <Image Src="/images/white-horse.jpg"
                       Alt="white horse"
                       Fill="true"
                       CssClass="object-cover"
                       Sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, (max-width: 1570px) 50vw, 33vw" />
            </div>
            <div class="p-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
                <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Understanding the <code>sizes</code> Prop:</h2>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                    <li><strong class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Mobile (up to 768px):</strong> Image takes full width (<code class="font-mono">100vw</code>).</li>
                    <li><strong class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Tablet (769px - 1200px):</strong> Image takes half width (<code class="font-mono">50vw</code>).</li>
                    <li><strong class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Large Tablet/Small Desktop (1201px - 1570px):</strong> Image takes half width (<code class="font-mono">50vw</code>).</li>
                    <li><strong class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Desktop (above 1570px):</strong> Image takes one-third width (<code class="font-mono">33vw</code>).</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 rounded-md bg-gray-100 p-4">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Code Example for <code>sizes</code></h3>
                <pre class="bg-gray-200 rounded-md overflow-x-auto p-2 font-mono text-sm text-gray-900"><code>
&lt;Image
    Src="/responsive-image.jpg"
    Alt="Responsive image"
    Fill="true"
    AspectRatio="(16, 9)"
    Sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw,
           (max-width: 1200px) 50vw,
           33vw"
    CssClass="object-cover" /&gt;
</code></pre>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="py-8 border-t border-gray-200">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-6">Maintaining Aspect Ratio with the <code>AspectRatio</code> Prop</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
                The <code>AspectRatio</code> prop ensures your images maintain their intended proportions during loading and resizing, preventing layout shifts. Combine it with <code>Fill</code> to make the image scale within its container while respecting the ratio.
            </p>

            <div class="mb-8 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden border border-gray-200">
                <div class="relative bg-gray-100">
                    <Image Src="/images/landscape.jpg"
                           Alt="Landscape with Aspect Ratio"
                           Fill="true"
                           AspectRatio="(16, 9)"
                           CssClass="object-cover" />
                </div>
                <div class="p-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
                    <p>This image uses an <code>AspectRatio</code> of <code class="font-mono">(16, 9)</code>. The container will maintain this ratio, and the image will fill it using <code>object-cover</code>.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="mt-4 rounded-md bg-gray-100 p-4">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Code Example for <code>AspectRatio</code> Prop</h3>
                    <pre class="bg-gray-200 rounded-md overflow-x-auto p-2 font-mono text-sm text-gray-900"><code>
&lt;Image
    Src="/landscape.jpg"
    Alt="Landscape with fixed aspect ratio"
    Fill="true"
    AspectRatio="(16, 9)" &lt;!-- (AspectWidth, AspectHeight) --&gt
    CssClass="object-cover" /&gt;
</code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden border border-gray-200">
                <div class="relative" style="aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;">
                    <Image Src="/images/landscape.jpg"
                           Alt="Landscape with CSS Aspect Ratio"
                           Fill="true"
                           CssClass="object-cover" />
                </div>
                <div class="p-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
                    <p>You can also control aspect ratio using CSS with <code class="font-mono">style="aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;"</code> or Tailwind CSS classes like <code class="font-mono">aspect-w-16 aspect-h-9</code>.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="mt-4 rounded-md bg-gray-100 p-4">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Code Example with CSS <code>aspect-ratio</code></h3>
                    <pre class="bg-gray-200 rounded-md overflow-x-auto p-2 font-mono text-sm text-gray-900"><code>
&lt;div style="position:relative; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;"> &lt;!-- or class="aspect-w-16 aspect-h-9" --&gt
    &lt;Image
        Src="/landscape.jpg"
        Alt="Landscape with CSS aspect ratio"
        Fill="true"
        CssClass="object-cover" /&gt;
&lt;/div>
</code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </section>
</div> 